2025-04-29 - CALSTIS:
	- Replaces most sprintf with snprintf - 640
	- Born from #639 - As I was replacing the custom argument parsers I uncovered several conditions 
	  that lead straight to segfaults due to buffer overflows. Most often they cropped up when the trailer
	  file functions (`trlerror`, `trlwarn`) were attempting to report messages larger than the line buffer.
	- This also adjusts the size of several buffers to accommodate the expected input, otherwise they would 
	  likely be truncated at run-time.

